UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407675900445
AB  - In this paper we have considered the problem of estimating the parameters of two seemingly unrelated regression equations when the number of available observations on all the variables in the first equation exceeds the number of available observations on all the variables in the second equation. We have shown how, within the Bayesian framework, extra observations on all the variables in the first equation can be readily and formally utilized in obtaining the exact or an approximate posterior distributions of all the coefficients including those in the second equation.
