T1  - A note on least squares estimation and the blue in a generalized linear regression model
AU  - Schönfeld, Peter
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 3
IS  - 2
SP  - 189
EP  - 197
PY  - 1975
DA  - 1975/05/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(75)90047-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407675900470
AB  - In a generalized linear regression model, least squares and Gauss-Markov estimators differ, in general, if the variance-covariance matrix of the disturbances is singular. In the present note it is shown that, nevertheless, the conventional least squares procedure leads to a Gauss-Markov estimator if it is applied to a modified model which results from adding dummy constraints to the original model. These constraints reflect the effects of the singularity of the variance- convariance matrix. As a consequence, a Gauss-Markov estimate may always be obtained by standard least squares minimization, which offers considerable computational advantages.
